1
00:00:01,599 --> 00:00:03,116
Will you really be okay?

2
00:00:03,116 --> 00:00:07,576
Of course, you know I can act. I'm sure I won't get caught.

3
00:00:07,576 --> 00:00:10,076
[Episode 6]

4
00:00:36,094 --> 00:00:38,193
D-Dad!

5
00:00:39,375 --> 00:00:41,875
Did you go exercise?

6
00:00:44,669 --> 00:00:46,369
Yes.

7
00:00:51,784 --> 00:00:53,484
Jin Ah.

8
00:00:55,257 --> 00:00:57,957
I want you to...

9
00:01:05,598 --> 00:01:08,599
I... lied to you.

10
00:01:18,634 --> 00:01:20,834
Is it something that could...

11
00:01:25,106 --> 00:01:27,406
make me disappointed in you?

12
00:01:31,942 --> 00:01:33,542
Yes.

13
00:01:42,791 --> 00:01:45,691
But you might not be.

14
00:01:48,277 --> 00:01:51,577
I'm going to try to make it so that you're not.

15
00:01:52,753 --> 00:01:58,131
I can't... tell you anything now.

16
00:02:02,900 --> 00:02:05,640
Please wait a little bit.

17
00:02:05,640 --> 00:02:08,541
I'll tell you everything later.

18
00:02:10,171 --> 00:02:12,571
Until then...

19
00:02:13,941 --> 00:02:16,641
please trust me and wait.

20
00:02:21,780 --> 00:02:23,610
Are you angry?

21
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:26,340
I mean...

22
00:02:27,444 --> 00:02:30,344
Why are you sitting there with your head bowed?

23
00:02:39,583 --> 00:02:42,083
What are you two doing?

24
00:02:42,083 --> 00:02:46,362
I just want to exercise with you. Is that something to pout about?

25
00:02:46,362 --> 00:02:50,493
I'm just saying it for your health.

26
00:02:50,493 --> 00:02:52,262
Don't you know that it's all for you?

27
00:02:52,262 --> 00:02:53,904
You're worrying about strange things.

28
00:02:53,904 --> 00:02:56,226
She's young. She can handle it herself.

29
00:02:56,227 --> 00:02:58,613
Why are you bothering her on her day off?

30
00:02:58,613 --> 00:03:01,289
Stop being silly and get out.

31
00:03:01,289 --> 00:03:05,889
Goodness, why are you acting so out of character?

32
00:03:05,889 --> 00:03:07,631
And why are you standing there like that?

33
00:03:07,632 --> 00:03:12,232
Oh my. Did you get changed to go with him?

34
00:03:12,232 --> 00:03:13,881
I'll get going.

35
00:03:13,881 --> 00:03:18,282
If you don't want to go, why are you forcing yourself to go?

36
00:03:25,670 --> 00:03:32,120
♫ Sometimes it's hard to be a woman ♫

37
00:03:34,710 --> 00:03:41,000
♫ Giving all your love to just one man♫

38
00:03:43,880 --> 00:03:52,770
♫ You'll have the bad times and he'll have the good times ♫

39
00:03:52,770 --> 00:03:59,140
♫ Doing things that you don't understand ♫

40
00:04:02,260 --> 00:04:08,120
♫ But if you love him, you'll forgive him ♫

41
00:04:11,010 --> 00:04:18,070
♫ Even though he's hard to understand ♫

42
00:04:19,990 --> 00:04:29,050
♫ And if you love him, oh, be proud of him ♫

43
00:04:29,050 --> 00:04:35,450
♫ 'Cause after all he's just a man ♫

44
00:04:38,130 --> 00:04:47,660
♫ Stand by your man. Give him two arms to cling to ♫

45
00:04:47,660 --> 00:04:56,070
♫ And something warm to come to when nights are cold and lonely ♫

46
00:04:56,070 --> 00:05:00,567
♫ Stand by your man ♫

47
00:05:00,567 --> 00:05:02,767
It's been two hours, right?

48
00:05:04,421 --> 00:05:06,420
I think so.

49
00:05:07,446 --> 00:05:10,146
Let's go then.

50
00:05:11,039 --> 00:05:12,639
Dad.

51
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:20,590
♫ Stand by your man ♫

52
00:05:23,390 --> 00:05:32,590
♫ Stand by your man and show the world you love him ♫

53
00:05:32,590 --> 00:05:34,110
♫ Keep giving all... ♫

54
00:05:34,113 --> 00:05:36,913
Why do you keep saying that everything's okay?

55
00:05:37,626 --> 00:05:39,826
What did he say?

56
00:05:42,386 --> 00:05:45,287
Don't suffer by yourself.

57
00:05:46,696 --> 00:05:48,784
I'm really not.

58
00:05:48,785 --> 00:05:52,485
I wish he would've just yelled at me.

59
00:05:53,138 --> 00:05:55,938
I shouldn't have held you back yesterday.

60
00:05:57,377 --> 00:06:00,625
I'm not a woman who can be held back, even if you try.

61
00:06:00,626 --> 00:06:03,925
I stayed because I wanted to.

62
00:06:03,925 --> 00:06:06,760
I should be the one comforting you, not the other way around.

63
00:06:06,760 --> 00:06:11,360
It's not trying to comfort you. I'm just telling you the truth.

64
00:06:13,388 --> 00:06:15,100
You're so beautiful.

65
00:06:15,850 --> 00:06:17,950
I know that.

66
00:06:19,900 --> 00:06:22,837
When will you show me that pretty face of yours?

67
00:06:22,838 --> 00:06:24,347
I'll come pick you up later.

68
00:06:24,348 --> 00:06:28,848
I should stay home today. I do have a conscience, after all.

69
00:06:34,617 --> 00:06:39,217
Don't worry. I can do a good job.

70
00:06:39,217 --> 00:06:41,111
I have you.

71
00:06:42,717 --> 00:06:44,637
Next to me...

72
00:06:44,637 --> 00:06:50,126
I have Seo Jun Hui, so what would I be scared of?

73
00:06:50,127 --> 00:06:52,327
I'm not at all afraid.

74
00:06:55,912 --> 00:06:58,512
- Yun Jin Ah.
- Yes?

75
00:06:59,454 --> 00:07:01,254
I love you.

76
00:07:08,083 --> 00:07:10,483
I really love you a lot.

77
00:07:29,900 --> 00:07:36,780
♫ I feel you now from here ♫

78
00:07:36,780 --> 00:07:43,480
♫ Our time is not done yet ♫

79
00:07:43,480 --> 00:07:49,640
♫ You've given me my fullest heart ♫

80
00:07:49,640 --> 00:07:56,100
♫ We'll never be apart ♫

81
00:08:06,750 --> 00:08:13,300
♫ I'm breathing through you now ♫

82
00:08:13,300 --> 00:08:20,070
♫ The love we have so true ♫

83
00:08:20,070 --> 00:08:26,720
♫ I never thought that I could need someone ♫

84
00:08:26,720 --> 00:08:33,080
♫ the way I do ♫

85
00:08:44,354 --> 00:08:46,371
[I want to see you soon.]

86
00:08:46,372 --> 00:08:48,781
[Me too. Take your time coming, but I am dying to see you.]

87
00:08:48,782 --> 00:08:50,454
[Dad is going to bed! I'll run right over.]

88
00:08:50,455 --> 00:08:51,850
[Come soon. I'll hug you.]

89
00:08:51,851 --> 00:08:56,051
[We just hung up, but I want to hear your voice and see you again.]

90
00:08:58,488 --> 00:09:01,388
Have you eaten?

91
00:09:01,388 --> 00:09:03,222
I don't have an appetite.

92
00:09:03,222 --> 00:09:05,623
Have you not eaten all day?

93
00:09:05,623 --> 00:09:07,160
Oh no.

94
00:09:07,161 --> 00:09:11,261
Do you want anything? Tell me, I'll go buy it for you.

95
00:09:11,772 --> 00:09:13,828
Not really.

96
00:09:13,828 --> 00:09:18,049
You should eat something. Can't you think of anything?

97
00:09:18,050 --> 00:09:19,780
No.

98
00:09:20,981 --> 00:09:24,432
I do feel like eating something spicy.

99
00:09:24,433 --> 00:09:26,338
"Something spicy"?

100
00:09:26,339 --> 00:09:28,939
You must want kimchi stew.

101
00:09:29,910 --> 00:09:31,664
Now that you mention it, I'm really craving it.

102
00:09:31,665 --> 00:09:34,255
We should go to Mom's place then. You love her kimchi stew.

103
00:09:34,256 --> 00:09:36,273
Gosh, why make such a fuss?

104
00:09:36,274 --> 00:09:41,869
Mom always says that we should let her know if we want to eat anything.

105
00:09:41,870 --> 00:09:43,943
Give me your phone. I should call Jin Ah first.

106
00:09:43,944 --> 00:09:46,745
Wait, I'm looking at something.

107
00:09:47,699 --> 00:09:51,600
Hold on. I'll tell the manager that I'm leaving and get my bag.

108
00:09:58,838 --> 00:10:01,559
- You're here.
- Mom.

109
00:10:01,560 --> 00:10:04,781
Why do you always bring something when you come, like some stranger?

110
00:10:04,781 --> 00:10:07,081
It's just fruit.

111
00:10:08,169 --> 00:10:10,854
- Dad, we're here.
- Oh, hi.

112
00:10:10,854 --> 00:10:12,919
- Hello.
- Come on in.

113
00:10:12,920 --> 00:10:17,259
He was excited to day drink, so he's been grilling meat.

114
00:10:17,259 --> 00:10:19,767
I feel the same as Dad...

115
00:10:19,767 --> 00:10:20,969
What about Yun Jin Ah?

116
00:10:20,969 --> 00:10:22,391
She's still sleeping.

117
00:10:22,392 --> 00:10:24,792
When I'm here?

118
00:10:36,933 --> 00:10:38,923
You wench!

119
00:10:38,923 --> 00:10:42,322
Oh, you scared me! What is this?

120
00:10:42,322 --> 00:10:43,770
- Hey.
- What?

121
00:10:43,770 --> 00:10:45,390
What are you doing?

122
00:10:45,390 --> 00:10:48,449
What are you doing here? You didn't even call.

123
00:10:48,449 --> 00:10:49,929
Oh my! Oh!

124
00:10:49,930 --> 00:10:52,430
Hey! Oh no.

125
00:10:53,328 --> 00:10:54,967
- Ouch!
- Sorry, sorry.

126
00:10:54,968 --> 00:10:57,769
When... when did you get here?

127
00:10:58,626 --> 00:11:01,189
I called Mom before coming.

128
00:11:01,189 --> 00:11:06,989
Hey, I know it's your day off, but how can you still be sleeping?

129
00:11:07,789 --> 00:11:09,589
What did you do yesterday?

130
00:11:10,405 --> 00:11:12,982
What... what would I do?

131
00:11:12,983 --> 00:11:14,775
Stuttering?

132
00:11:14,776 --> 00:11:17,231
You're acting very suspicious.

133
00:11:17,232 --> 00:11:19,496
Tell the truth right this instant!

134
00:11:19,496 --> 00:11:21,075
What truth!

135
00:11:21,075 --> 00:11:25,175
Hey... you!

136
00:11:30,459 --> 00:11:32,638
You made so much kimchi stew.

137
00:11:32,638 --> 00:11:34,783
You said Jun Hui wanted it.

138
00:11:34,783 --> 00:11:37,983
He didn't have an appetite, but I think he will eat very well.

139
00:11:51,305 --> 00:11:53,405
It's taking so long.

140
00:12:13,805 --> 00:12:15,805
I need to make a phone call.

141
00:12:21,752 --> 00:12:23,894
Why did you come?

142
00:12:23,894 --> 00:12:25,994
Hey, are you crazy?

143
00:12:25,995 --> 00:12:27,912
I was dying to see you. What could I do?

144
00:12:27,913 --> 00:12:29,533
You're really crazy!

145
00:12:29,534 --> 00:12:30,708
Yes, I am.

146
00:12:30,709 --> 00:12:32,909
What? Hey!

147
00:12:34,800 --> 00:12:36,156
Seriously, get out.

148
00:12:36,156 --> 00:12:38,557
- Why?
- What do you mean "Why"?

149
00:12:39,534 --> 00:12:41,358
Why didn't you say anything though?

150
00:12:41,358 --> 00:12:42,958
Say what?

151
00:12:43,838 --> 00:12:45,939
I told you that I loved you.

152
00:12:46,500 --> 00:12:48,060
Ah...

153
00:12:48,871 --> 00:12:50,471
"Ah"?

154
00:12:51,816 --> 00:12:53,740
Oh?

155
00:12:53,741 --> 00:12:55,340
Oh, look at you.

156
00:12:55,341 --> 00:12:56,916
"Look at you"?

157
00:12:56,916 --> 00:12:58,740
Look at you.

158
00:12:59,601 --> 00:13:01,590
Where did they go?

159
00:13:03,173 --> 00:13:04,773
What the heck? What are you doing?

160
00:13:04,773 --> 00:13:08,266
Gosh, I told him to leave. What's he doing in my room?

161
00:13:08,266 --> 00:13:10,345
Listen to your elders, would you?

162
00:13:10,345 --> 00:13:13,302
- When will you grow up?
- I know.

163
00:13:13,302 --> 00:13:16,001
I'm hungry. Let's hurry up and eat.

164
00:13:17,726 --> 00:13:21,521
Jun Hui, eat a lot.

165
00:13:21,521 --> 00:13:24,881
And come over whenever you feel like having a home-cooked meal.

166
00:13:24,881 --> 00:13:27,172
It doesn't matter if no one is home.

167
00:13:27,172 --> 00:13:29,595
You can help yourself to whatever you want.

168
00:13:29,596 --> 00:13:31,096
I will.

169
00:13:32,459 --> 00:13:34,663
No matter what I make for him, he doesn't seem satisfied.

170
00:13:34,664 --> 00:13:37,468
I think he's only ravenous for your cooking.

171
00:13:37,468 --> 00:13:39,929
Wait until he gets married. He'll only want his wife's food.

172
00:13:39,929 --> 00:13:43,179
That depends on who he marries.

173
00:13:43,180 --> 00:13:47,361
An employee at Jin Ah's company has been interested in Jun Hui lately.

174
00:13:47,361 --> 00:13:49,172
Oh, really? Who is she?

175
00:13:49,172 --> 00:13:51,643
She's the section chief who took over my store for Jin Ah.

176
00:13:51,643 --> 00:13:53,310
Her name is Kang Se Yeong.

177
00:13:53,310 --> 00:13:56,610
She's already laying down the foundation by sucking up to me.

178
00:13:58,414 --> 00:14:01,214
- You noticed, too, right?
- I did.

179
00:14:02,746 --> 00:14:04,257
Oh, is that right?

180
00:14:04,257 --> 00:14:06,358
I knew as soon as I met her.

181
00:14:07,276 --> 00:14:09,576
You must've been really happy.

182
00:14:10,410 --> 00:14:15,348
Yun Jin Ah sure is dense. I knew right away, too.

183
00:14:15,348 --> 00:14:16,650
I guess I'm the only one who didn't.

184
00:14:16,650 --> 00:14:18,707
She's popular in the building because she's so pretty.

185
00:14:18,707 --> 00:14:19,989
I see.

186
00:14:19,990 --> 00:14:23,813
So she has good looks. What is her family like?

187
00:14:23,814 --> 00:14:24,918
Mom.

188
00:14:24,918 --> 00:14:27,869
What? Do you know how important that is?

189
00:14:27,870 --> 00:14:29,418
What do her parents do?

190
00:14:29,419 --> 00:14:31,919
How would I know that?

191
00:14:32,578 --> 00:14:35,789
Jun Hui, you know...

192
00:14:35,790 --> 00:14:38,778
when you date someone, it can't just be about liking them.

193
00:14:38,778 --> 00:14:42,878
You have to look at that person's parents, siblings, and the entire family.

194
00:14:43,428 --> 00:14:45,127
But what's so great about us?

195
00:14:45,128 --> 00:14:46,715
That's why you have to be even more mindful.

196
00:14:46,715 --> 00:14:50,015
At least one side of the family should have something.

197
00:14:51,030 --> 00:14:53,831
Stop talking about frivolous things.

198
00:14:54,427 --> 00:14:56,165
Let's just eat.

199
00:14:56,166 --> 00:15:00,626
How is that frivolous? It's about their future.

200
00:15:00,626 --> 00:15:03,018
They're all grown up now. They can handle it on their own.

201
00:15:03,018 --> 00:15:05,217
Why must you make them uncomfortable?

202
00:15:05,218 --> 00:15:06,870
Oh my.

203
00:15:07,519 --> 00:15:10,462
Did you two find that offensive?

204
00:15:10,462 --> 00:15:12,194
Will you keep going?

205
00:15:12,194 --> 00:15:13,714
Then I'll just go to my room.

206
00:15:13,714 --> 00:15:15,620
Jin Ah, relax.

207
00:15:15,621 --> 00:15:18,189
What? She's just trying to help.

208
00:15:18,190 --> 00:15:20,972
That's right. I am.

209
00:15:20,973 --> 00:15:24,029
I guess what I'm saying may sound unpleasant.

210
00:15:24,030 --> 00:15:27,727
But it's not like I have any other intention. It's all to help Jun Hui.

211
00:15:27,727 --> 00:15:29,856
Jun Hui, you understand, right?

212
00:15:29,857 --> 00:15:32,029
Of course. I'm thankful.

213
00:15:32,030 --> 00:15:36,311
Also, don't worry about it. I'll handle it well on my own.

214
00:15:36,311 --> 00:15:39,611
Okay. Eat this too, Jun Hui.

215
00:15:49,860 --> 00:15:52,790
Section Chief, big news.

216
00:15:52,790 --> 00:15:54,654
It happened in the purchasing team too.

217
00:15:54,655 --> 00:15:55,585
What did?

218
00:15:55,585 --> 00:15:57,794
The resource team and purchasing team went for dinner.

219
00:15:57,795 --> 00:16:00,384
Section Chief Choi declined Manager Oh's drink.

220
00:16:00,384 --> 00:16:04,192
"Don't force me. I'll sue you for human rights violation."

221
00:16:04,192 --> 00:16:05,584
She said that.

222
00:16:05,585 --> 00:16:09,443
Wow, is this Yun Jin Ah's butterfly effect?

223
00:16:09,444 --> 00:16:11,842
It really was out of the blue.

224
00:16:11,843 --> 00:16:15,802
Who knew our Yun Tambourine could do something so bold?

225
00:16:15,803 --> 00:16:18,312
No one could have imagined it.

226
00:16:18,312 --> 00:16:20,741
What could have caused her to change?

227
00:16:20,742 --> 00:16:23,491
Whatever the reason, we should applaud it.

228
00:16:23,492 --> 00:16:27,882
I hope the backlash doesn't fall on us.

229
00:16:27,882 --> 00:16:29,494
I'm worried about that, too.

230
00:16:29,495 --> 00:16:31,534
I don't think the higher-ups will stay put.

231
00:16:31,535 --> 00:16:33,433
Let them try.

232
00:16:33,434 --> 00:16:36,134
There's no way I'm letting it go this time.

233
00:16:50,012 --> 00:16:53,112
[Announcement: Chairman's dinner. All female employees are invited.]

234
00:17:27,422 --> 00:17:29,223
Come in.

235
00:17:40,360 --> 00:17:42,360
Did you see the announcement?

236
00:17:43,211 --> 00:17:47,114
Discuss it with the female employees and choose a place for the dinner.

237
00:17:47,114 --> 00:17:48,614
Okay.

238
00:17:49,155 --> 00:17:50,855
One more thing.

239
00:17:51,563 --> 00:17:58,293
Any issues with the company, especially any discomfort they experience from discrimination...

240
00:17:58,293 --> 00:18:01,778
Get the female employees' opinions on it and bring a report on it.

241
00:18:02,934 --> 00:18:04,834
I understand.

242
00:18:05,800 --> 00:18:09,152
Tell them that it will be anonymous, so they can name any perpetrators.

243
00:18:09,153 --> 00:18:13,622
Chairman Jo, wouldn't it be unfair to only listen to one side?

244
00:18:13,622 --> 00:18:16,822
Dealing with the situation will be the next step.

245
00:18:18,502 --> 00:18:22,503
Why? Is there something you feel guilty about?

246
00:18:23,954 --> 00:18:26,454
Only the victims would know.

247
00:18:38,805 --> 00:18:41,505
Oh my. Where are you off to?

248
00:18:42,392 --> 00:18:43,792
Yes.

249
00:18:44,550 --> 00:18:46,300
No.

250
00:18:46,300 --> 00:18:48,392
"Love U"?

251
00:18:48,392 --> 00:18:49,486
Do you want to die?

252
00:18:49,486 --> 00:18:51,555
So you do have a girlfriend.

253
00:18:51,555 --> 00:18:53,103
Mind your own business.

254
00:18:53,104 --> 00:18:54,981
Who is it?

255
00:18:54,981 --> 00:18:56,890
Are you possibly...

256
00:18:57,481 --> 00:18:58,869
What?

257
00:18:58,869 --> 00:19:01,169
Are you seeing a married woman?

258
00:19:02,217 --> 00:19:05,369
Judging from how annoyed you look, I must be right.

259
00:19:05,369 --> 00:19:07,068
Who is she?

260
00:19:07,768 --> 00:19:12,068
You still have time, so don't drive too fast.

261
00:19:13,450 --> 00:19:16,199
I miss you, too.

262
00:19:16,199 --> 00:19:19,200
Okay. See you later.

263
00:19:21,881 --> 00:19:25,798
I had to contact the office so I was talking to my colleague.

